The paper discusses the performance of Convolutional Low-Density-Parity-Check (LDPC) ensembles, which are commonly used in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also uses combinatorial and replica methods, which are common in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The concept of coupled mean field graphical models is also discussed, which is relevant to network engineering (cs.NE) and social networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the behavior of growth rates, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
